bug.short_desc: Search bar leaves a black box when scrolling down

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 524320 [screenshot] black box when scrolling bar with search bar showing
Build identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.2a1pre) Gecko/20110406 Firefox/4.2a1pre
1. Open a page that you can scroll (e.g. https://wiki.mozilla.org/Main_Page) 2. Press Cmd + F to open the find bar 3. Scroll down
The problem is that when you scroll down you will see a black box where the search bar was initially drawn.
If you hover the URL links the drawing of the black box would flick.
I started seeing this late last week.

Indeed.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 647315 ***
